.TH SHELL @ "September 19, 2023"  "ALX SWE" "Project 0x16" 
"C - simple_shell - man page"

.SH NAME
.B simple_shell
\- simple UNIX command interpreter written in C 

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
[options] [file]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B simple_shell
is a command language interpreter that executes commands read from the standard input.
It is a clone of the sh shell.

.SH RETURN VALUE
The shell always returns the status of the previously executed command (0 if no command was executed).
Non-zero values indicate exit failure codes.

.SH PATH
The shell looks in the PATH environment variable to locate executable program files.

.SH INVOCATION
.B simple_shell
can be invoked both interactively and non-interactively.
When invoked with standard input not connected to a terminal, it reads and executes received commands in order.

If
.B simple_shell
is invoked with standard input connected to a terminal, it opens an interactive shell.
When executing interactively, the shell displays the prompt "($)" when it is ready to read a command.

.SH OPTIONS
.B simple_shell
Command options are typed after the main command, separated by a space and a '-' symbol.

.SH EXAMPLES
To run a command with options, use the following format:
.BR ./hsh [command] [options]
For example:
.BR $ ls -l

